message.content: A picket fence is a type of fence typically made with evenly spaced, vertical wooden slats. The slats may be pointed, round, or flat-topped. The fence may have a decorative design on top or be left plain. Picket fences are often painted white or left natural for a rustic look. They are commonly found in residential areas, usually surrounding a front yard or garden. Picket fences are associated with traditional decor and evoke a sense of charm and friendliness. Overall, picket fences have a classic and timeless appearance.
